{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κάπηλος</b> [ᾰ], ὁ<br /> (also ἡ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 9.180 (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus))\">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>], <b>retail-dealer, huckster</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.94, 2.141, 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 1, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἔμπορος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 22.21, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.5.42, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 371d, “Prt.” 314a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also opposed to the producer (αὐτοπώλης), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Sph.” 231d, “Plt.” 260c \">Refs</a>]; applied to Darius, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.89 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἀσπίδων, ὅπλων, <b>a dealer in</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 447, 1209. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> especially <b>tavern-keeper</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 347, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator “Fragmenta” 1, “PMagd.” 26.2 (3rd c.BC), “PTeb.” 612 (1st-2nd c.AD), 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Herm.” 58, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, κ. πονηρίας <b>dealer in petty</b>roguery, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.46. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> as <i>adjective</i>, ος, ον, ={καπηλικός},{βίος} [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 9.25 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>cheating, knavish</b>, κ. προσφέρων τεχνήματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 322; κ. φρόνημα “Comica Adespota” 867. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumb